CONSTRAINTS: Use ONLY the field names, types, and enum values from the data dictionary above. Do NOT invent new fields or rename existing ones.

% Role & Scope
This module is the foundational shared data contract for all six generation quality modules. It defines Pydantic v2 models for every entity in the data dictionary: `GenerationSourceContract` (UUID-keyed root artifact persisted to `.pdd/generation-contracts/{run_id}.json`), `FeatureRequirement`, `ExampleClassification`, `InterfaceFact`, `WiringCheckResult`, `TestQualityFinding`, `ReadinessFinding`, `GenerationAuditRecord`, and `RequirementAuditEntry`. It also exports `create_source_contract`, `load_source_contract`, and `save_source_contract` for file-based JSON persistence.

% Requirements
1. Define all 9 enums as `str, Enum` subclasses with lowercase string values from the data dictionary: `RequirementPriority` (`p0`, `p1`), `FindingSeverity` (`blocker`, `warning`), `ExampleKind` (`illustrative`, `exhaustive`, `unknown`), `RequirementKind` (`api`, `route`, `schema`, `ui`, `cli`, `job`, `test`, `script`), `InterfaceFactKind` (`function`, `class_field`, `export`, `endpoint`, `config_key`, `component_prop`), `WiringCheckKind` (`handler_registration`, `route_reachability`, `config_declaration`, `module_test_coverage`, `script_executable`), `WiringStatus` (`pass_` with value `"pass"` to avoid Python keyword, `warn`, `fail`), `TestQualityFindingKind` (`brittle_selector`, `private_impl_assertion`, `exact_dynamic_text`, `no_async_polling`), `AuditEntryStatus` (`covered`, `partial`, `skipped`, `waived`).
2. Define all 9 Pydantic v2 `BaseModel` subclasses using `model_config = ConfigDict(use_enum_values=True)` for automatic enum serialization. Fields must exactly match the data dictionary (names, types, required/optional, defaults).
3. Add `model_validator(mode='after')` on `FeatureRequirement` to enforce that `acceptance_criteria` is non-empty when `priority == "p0"`.
4. `RequirementAuditEntry.gate_results: List[Union[WiringCheckResult, TestQualityFinding]]` — use `Annotated` with `Field(discriminator=...)` or a plain `Union` — whichever round-trips cleanly via `model_dump(mode='json')`.
5. Call `model_rebuild()` on all models after class definitions to resolve forward references.
6. Export module-level constant `GENERATION_SOURCE_CONTRACT_SCHEMA_VERSION: int = 1`.
7. Implement `create_source_contract(run_id=None, prd_text=None) -> GenerationSourceContract`: generates `str(uuid.uuid4())` if `run_id` is `None`.
8. Implement `load_source_contract(run_id, base_dir=Path('.pdd/generation-contracts')) -> GenerationSourceContract`: resolves `base_dir / f"{run_id}.json"`, reads UTF-8 text, parses with `GenerationSourceContract.model_validate_json(text)`. Raises `FileNotFoundError` if path missing, propagates `ValidationError` on bad JSON.
9. Implement `save_source_contract(contract, base_dir=Path('.pdd/generation-contracts')) -> Path`: serializes with `json.dumps(contract.model_dump(mode='json'), indent=2)`, writes UTF-8 to `base_dir / f"{contract.run_id}.json"`, calls `mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)` first, returns the `Path`.
10. Use `from __future__ import annotations` at top. Stdlib-only imports: `json`, `uuid`, `pathlib`, `enum`, `typing`. Pydantic v2 imports: `BaseModel`, `ConfigDict`, `Field`, `field_validator`, `model_validator`.

% Dependencies
