% Instructions
- Define enums at the top of the file, before any model classes, so models can reference them.
- Use `class WiringStatus(str, Enum): PASS_ = "pass"; WARN = "warn"; FAIL = "fail"` — the member name is `PASS_` but the serialized value is `"pass"`.
- `GenerationSourceContract` stores `schema_version: int = Field(default=1)` and `grounded_from_contract: bool = Field(default=False)`.
- `InterfaceFact.signature` is `Optional[str] = None` — `None` for non-callable facts like class fields or config keys.
- All list fields default to `Field(default_factory=list)`.
- Keep model definitions in dependency order: enums → leaf models (FeatureRequirement, ExampleClassification, InterfaceFact, WiringCheckResult, TestQualityFinding, ReadinessFinding) → container models (GenerationSourceContract, RequirementAuditEntry, GenerationAuditRecord).

% Deliverables
- Single file: `pdd/generation_source_contract.py`
- All 9 enums and 9 Pydantic v2 models
- Three persistence functions: `create_source_contract`, `load_source_contract`, `save_source_contract`
- Module constant: `GENERATION_SOURCE_CONTRACT_SCHEMA_VERSION = 1`
- Full docstrings and type hints throughout
